<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{2}{y}=-{46}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{3}{x}-{y}=-{19}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},-{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -3. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{3}}{{7}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{3}}}{{7}}{\left({7}{x}+-{2}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{3}}}{{7}}{\left(-{46}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({3}\right)}{x}+{0.85714285714286}{y}={19.714285714286}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{x}-{y}=-{19}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.14285714285714}{y}={0.71428571428571}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{0.71428571428571}}{{-{{0.14285714285714}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+-{2}{\left(-{5}\right)}=-{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{\left({10}\right)}=-{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{46}-{\left({10}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{56}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},-{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

